  "suggestion": "Clustering emerges when exploration is low relative to resource attraction; diversity fails when all genomes converge. Decouple motion from consumption.; Spatial composition (0.3) is critical: organisms cluster around resources rather than exploring the full world. Efficiency (0.529) is weak: particle count is high relative to energy gain. The formBeauty and proportionHarmony are strong, but diversityOfForms (0.457) lacks variety. Solution: (1) Increase moveSpeed and explorationDrive to decouple movement from resource-seeking, spreading organisms spatially. (2) Reduce resourceAttraction on types that cluster, forcing them to explore. (3) Increase energyConserve across the board to improve energy-per-particle efficiency. This spreads the population spatially and reduces wasted particles.",
